  Locus:
    Page: 348
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Past
---
If you are pained by any external thing, it is not this thing that disturbs
you, but your own judgement about it. It is in your power to erase this
judgement now. If anything in your own nature gives you pain, you are who
hinders you from correcting your opinion.
